# Introduction

This is a brief introduction into `git` and how to use it for daily work.

A nice online resource: <https://git-scm.com/learn>.

In this lecture I want to cover the most basic `git` usages like:

* `git commit|pull|push|tag|log|rebase|stash|worktree`

Workflows:

* **fork** & **PRs** (Pull Requests), **issues** (markdown) and **documentation** (README.md)

Tools:

* `git`/`tig` and web tools

## Initializes a new Git repository

* `git init` - Initializes a new Git repository.
* `git clone <repository-url>` - Clones a repository into a new directory.
* `git svn clone <repository-url>` - Imports an SVN repository into a new directory.

## Looking into existing git repositorries

* `git status` - Displays the state of the working directory and staging area.
* `git branch` - Lists all local branches.

* `git log` - Shows the commit history. Options: `--oneline`, `--graph`, `--decorate`.
* `tig` / `gitui` - command line tool, very handy

* `cat .git/config`

* `git diff` - Shows changes between commits, commit and working directory, etc.

